I pushed myself to the extreme on this day. I remember carrying my North Face up past The Treasury and thinking I did not have the stamina to even carry it on my back any longer. But, I had no choice...I was in Petra and there was no easy way out. The entrance to The Treasury is a long walk in itself— about 30 minutes and that’s just the beginning of it all. The human body is a miraculous wonder and the will of a person is even more amazing. For many years I wanted to visit Jordan and as luck would have it, I was in Petra sick off my ass. There was no way I was going to succumb to the bug I had. There was no way I traveled around the world to sit this moment out. 

Don’t get me wrong, I paid the price for this decision later that day. I barely mustered the energy to make it to the hotel and up to my room. I showered and slept for hours. Mind you, I made it to my hotel around noon, as the sun was running rampant at the time. You do NOT want to be outside in the desert around noon. I managed to sleep for 8 hours and woke up feeling much better and even ventured out for dinner—which is a whole other story in itself. 😉
